Configuring Git

$ git config --global user.name "My Name"
$ git config --global user.email myEmail@example.com




Creating a new repository - git init

$ cd Desktop/git_exercise/
$ git init




Checking the status - git status

$ git status






Staging - git add

$ git add hello.txt

$ git add -A

$ git status





Commiting - git commit

$ git commit -m "Initial commit."







Connecting to a remote repository - git remote add

$ git remote add origin https://github.com/tutorialzine/awesome-project


Remove origin
$ git remote rm/remove origin



Uploading to a server - git push

$ git push origin master

# adds all the files and folders of current directory to the remote repo





Cloning a repository - git clone

$ git clone https://github.com/tutorialzine/awesome-project







Getting changes from a server - git pull

$ git pull origin master






Creating new branches - git branch
$ git branch amazing_new_feature




Switching branches - git checkout

$ git branch

$ git checkout amazing_new_feature






Merging branches - git merge

$ git add feature.txt
$ git commit -m "New feature complete."

$ git checkout master

$git merge amazing_new_feature




delete branch

$git branch -d amazing_new_feature




Checking difference between commits

$ git log

$ git show b10cc123

$ git diff 09bd8cc..ba25c0ff




Reverting a file to a previous version

$ git checkout 09bd8cc1 hello.txt


Remove git repo

$rm -rf .git
$rm -rf git_folder


Unstage Git

$git reset HEAD file


create a new repository on the command line

echo "# mp" >> README.md
git init
git add README.md
git commit -m "first commit"
git remote add origin git@github.com:sharmisthaec/mp.git
git push -u origin master
                
                
                
forefully pull the origin to local repo

$ git pull origin master --allow-unrelated-histories